---
title: Mushroom Lo Mein with Green Beans and Sweet Ginger Sauce
description: Chinese-style lo mein gets a hearty and wholesome twist when you swap out the usual meaty suspects for mushrooms and veggies like carrots and green beans. In this recipe, you’ll practice stir-frying udon noodles in sauce until they brim with a savory soy, hoisin, and sesame-based flavor that explodes with each bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mushroom-lo-mein-706533a7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mushroom-lo-mein-4e182fb9.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 460 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 1.5 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 900 mg
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mushroom-lo-mein-59960040a2882a195d4e2bc2
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @green beans{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Peel and
mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Peel @carrots{1},
then cut in half lengthwise. Slice into thin half-moons. Trim, then slice
@mixed wild mushrooms{4%ounce}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping
greens and whites separate.

Whisk together @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1},
@hoisin sauce{1%tablespoon}, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @honey{1%teaspoon},
and @water{1/4%cup} in a #small bowl{} and set aside.

> We sent more hoisin sauce and honey than needed.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium
heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add @udon noodles{8%ounce} and
cook, tossing, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If pan seems dry, add a splash of water.

Remove noodles from pan and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, carrot,
and green beans. Cook, tossing occasionally, until lightly browned and softened,
~{5-7%minutes}. Add ginger, scallion whites, and garlic. Toss until fragrant,
~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Reduce heat to medium. Add sauce and noodles to pan. Toss everything until
well-coated and sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide lo mein between bowls. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.